title: Jones Appointed Vice-President
description: Wiliam Jones was appointed as vice-president for financial affairs. Jones' has twenty six yers of service as a business manager in NC.
subject: Finnacal affairs vice-president

title: Athletic Director Earns Doctorate
description: James W. Younge completed all the requirements for the Ed.D. degree at Temple University. He has been on the NCC falculty since 1949. He is the athletic director and assistant professor
subject: Athletic director

description: Twenty NCC students were nominated for "Who's Who Among Students in American Universites and Colleges", based on their academics, campus citzenship, etc.

subject: Representatives

subject: Government intership

subject: Bridge

description: 373 students and one faculty member of NCCU recieved awards for their scholarship, athletics, or involvement in campus activities

description: NCCU (once NCC) conducted a self-study of how well the college worked from a social, educational, and functional standpoint

subject: Political Advertisement

title: Traditionalism Seen Strong at NCC
description: Students felt as if negative occurrences and problems were being dismissed on campus because of traditionalism and that the campus needed to try and stay with the times if they wanted to become a better college
creator: Aaron R. Graham

description: Gregory Kannerstein, an NCC English instructor, reviewed the newspaper and made a few suggestions to help make the paper better
subject: Gregory Kannerstein's Review of the Newspaper

creator: Esther Silver

subject: Officers of 1967-68 SNEA

title: Speaker Praises Negro Lawyers
description: Maynard H. Jackson Jr. talks about the trials and tribulatons Black lawyers go through and praise them for helping the Black community even though it is difficult and largely unrewarding
subject: Black Lawyers

title: Student Named City Hall Intern
description: Dwight A. Yarborough gets named a summer intern in the Personel Department of the City of Durham sponsored by the Institute of Government in Chapel Hill
subject: New City Hall Intern

title: Nat'l Teachers Exam Set For July
description: North Carolina College was designated as a test center for administering the National Teacher Examinations on July 1, 1967, and people who wished to could take the test to see their knowledge in different areas of subject matter
subject: National Teacher Examinations

title: Law Student Gets National Office

subject: American Law Student Association

title: Freshman Holds News Conference

subject: First NCCU News Conference

title: NCC Sprinters Set 440 Record

subject: NCCU Track

title: Tennis Team Play In Hampton Event
description: North Carolina College's tennis team played hard but lost by a one-match margin to Hampton Institute
subject: NCCU Tennis

description: North Carolina College's tennis team had a 7-2 record in 1967, losing only to the Hampton Institute
subject: NCCU Tennis
